      "agentResultText": "Build succeeds. Here's a summary of everything that was done:\n\n### Changes Made\n\n1. **Installed `@clerk/nextjs@6.39.0`** — compatible with Next.js 14\n\n2. **`src/middleware.ts`** — Clerk middleware that protects `/dashboard` and `/settings` routes, requiring authentication. Public routes: `/`, `/sign-in`, `/sign-up`.\n\n3. **`src/app/layout.tsx`** — Wrapped the app in `<ClerkProvider>`. Nav now shows Dashboard/Settings links only when signed in (`<SignedIn>`), a `<UserButton>` for the signed-in user, and a Sign In link when signed out (`<SignedOut>`).\n\n4. **`src/app/sign-in/[[...sign-in]]/page.tsx`** — Clerk's `<SignIn>` component for email/password sign-in.\n\n5. **`src/app/sign-up/[[...sign-up]]/page.tsx`** — Clerk's `<SignUp>` component for email/password registration.\n\n6. **`prisma/schema.prisma`** — Added `clerkId String @unique` field to the `User` model.\n\n7. **`src/lib/current-user.ts`** — Helper that resolves the authenticated Clerk user to a database `User` record (auto-creates on first sign-in via `upsert`).\n\n8. **`src/app/dashboard/actions.ts`** — Uses `getCurrentUser()` instead of hardcoded `DEFAULT_USER_ID`. Posts are scoped to the authenticated user.\n\n9. **`src/app/dashboard/page.tsx`** — Fetches only the current user's posts.\n\n10. **`src/app/settings/page.tsx`** & **`actions.ts`** — Uses `getCurrentUser()` to load/update the authenticated user's profile.",
