      "agentResultText": "\n\nThis is already implemented. The middleware at `src/middleware.ts:5-8` does exactly this:\n\n```typescript\nexport default clerkMiddleware(async (auth, req) => {\n  if (isProtectedRoute(req)) {\n    await auth.protect();\n  }\n});\n```\n\nThe `createRouteMatcher` on line 3 matches `/dashboard(.*)` and `/settings(.*)`, and `auth.protect()` redirects unauthenticated users to the sign-in page (configured via `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL=/sign-in` in `.env`).\n\nNo changes needed — unauthenticated users are already redirected to `/sign-in` when trying to access `/dashboard` or `/settings`.",
